<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Probability-theoretic_definition_of_Category_Utility">Probability-theoretic definition of Category Utility</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Category_utility&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Probability-theoretic definition of Category Utility">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The <a href="/wiki/Probability-theoretic" class="mw-redirect" title="Probability-theoretic">probability-theoretic</a> definition of <i>category utility</i> given in <a href="#CITEREFFisher1987">Fisher (1987)</a> and <a href="#CITEREFWittenFrank2005">Witten &amp; Frank (2005)</a> is as follows:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle CU(C,F)={\tfrac {1}{p}}\sum _{c_{j}\in C}p(c_{j})\left[\sum _{f_{i}\in F}\sum _{k=1}^{m}p(f_{ik}|c_{j})^{2}-\sum _{f_{i}\in F}\sum _{k=1}^{m}p(f_{ik})^{2}\right]}">
