</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/463798c1ac00670698f20d24a8a4b9e1c60ac226" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:3.549ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \otimes F}"/></span>.  (Ordinality does <i>not</i> matter, because the mutual information is not sensitive to ordinality.)  In what follows, a term such as <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle p(F_{a}=v_{i})}">
