</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d62e4100b94c1939c67f2d4b8580d26c78106c44" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.089ex; width:5.52ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="p=2"/></span> we have the two-category case discussed above.  From the definition of <a href="/wiki/Mutual_information" title="Mutual information">mutual information</a> for discrete variables, the mutual information <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle I(F_{a};C)}">
