      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle CU(C,F)=\sum _{f_{i}\in F}\sum _{c_{j}\in C}p(f_{i}|c_{j})p(c_{j})\log p(f_{i}|c_{j})-\sum _{f_{i}\in F}p(f_{i})\log p(f_{i})}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/fa572db0812bdaba3e2a80c46464ce01c2223d1f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.671ex; width:65.471ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle CU(C,F)=\sum _{f_{i}\in F}\sum _{c_{j}\in C}p(f_{i}|c_{j})p(c_{j})\log p(f_{i}|c_{j})-\sum _{f_{i}\in F}p(f_{i})\log p(f_{i})}"/></span></dd></dl>
<p>This equation clearly has the same <b>form</b> as the (<span style="color:blue;">blue</span>) equation expressing the mutual information between the feature set and the category variable; the difference is that the sum <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \textstyle \sum _{f_{i}\in F}}">
